actices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDeathxReligious aspectsxBuddhism. 0aDeathxSocial aspectszNepalzHelmu. 0aHelambu Sherpa (Nepalese people)xReligion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  adeath, loss, grief, buddhism, religion, spirituality, tibet, nepal, helmu, helambu, sherpa, impermanence, anthropology, nonfiction, mourning, ritual, rites, hyolmo buddhists, trauma, grieving, identity, memory, agency, longing, bodiless, communication, attachment, care ethics, transference, consciousness, corpses, bodies, sensuality, consolation, healing, dissolution, cremation, ashes, afterlife, forgetting, folk practice, ceremony.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226355900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226355900/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles